"The scheduler\u2019s **memo gate** avoids re-running a node when its **type, version, config, and resolved inputs (by port \u2192 content-hash)** haven\u2019t changed. It checks a cached content hash from a previous run, and if the cached result still exists, it reuses it \u2014 making \u201cre-run only what changed\u201d and \u201cresume\u201d the same behaviour.\n\nIt lives in **`runtime/scheduler.py`** (the `_memo_sig` function computes the cache key, and the `run` function checks / stores it)."